                        <p>Elections in Germany are free. What does that mean?</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li> You can accept money if you choose a specific candidate for it.</li><br>
<li id="correct_answer"> <span> &#10004; The voter must not be influenced during the election, nor forced to cast a particular vote, and must not suffer any disadvantages as a result of the election. </span></li><br>
                            <li> Only people who have never been in prison are allowed to vote.</li><br>
                            <li> All eligible voters must vote.</li><br>
                        </ul><br>
